        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} bring ten days to the island, where we spend our annual &ldquo;downcoming vacation&rdquo; this time. It was extremely full at the airport, but since we had already checked in, we were able to give up our suitcases at the Self Bag drop and go straight to the security check. Fortunately, we didn't have to wait long and were able to make ourselves comfortable in the upper part of the airport. </p>
        <p> After a mini breakfast - it was just too early - we went to the gate. Fortunately, we caught places with more legroom and made ourselves more or less comfortable in series 8 after boarding. With almost 20 minutes delay we picked up and ended up in Tenerife S&uuml;d shortly after 11 a.m. The checks for Corona happened, it was time to wait at the suitcase band - this time they took a lot of time. </p>
        <p> When we had everything together, we went to the TUI bus. Here too we waited a while, and after almost 30 minutes of driving we finally arrived at the Riu Arecas Hotel. And here too it was said: wait-because there was a fire alarm exercise, and everything went very leisurely. There was drinks for this. </p>

